-- Czech Stocks: CEZ, Erste Group Bank Shares Are Active in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-03-14T16:23:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/czech-stocks-cez-erste-group-bank-shares-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
rose for a second day, gaining 0.7 percent to 999.6 by the close
in Prague.  The following were among the most active equities on Prague
Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the country’s biggest power utility, added
1.5 percent to 815 koruna, the highest level in a week.
Electricity for next-year delivery in Germany, where CEZ exports
part of its output, increased for a second day, rising to 52.90
euros per megawatt-hour.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   climbed as much as 2.8
percent to 464.8 koruna. European stocks rallied after the
 Federal Reserve  bolstered confidence in the U.S. banking system
and raised its assessment of the world’s largest economy. The
shares ended the day 0.5 percent weaker at 449.8 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
